\begin_layout Abstract
Millions of posts and reviews are posted every day on the social media websites
 where people share all kinds of information such as political opinions,
 product feedback, movies reviews, and other text that conveys the sentiment
 of the user.
 These online opinions have a great influence on our own decisions when
 we plan to buy a product, travel abroad or even read a book.
 This is because these activities consume our worthy resources in terms
 of time and money.
 This calls for tools to mine social data streams and extract useful information
 out of it.
 Towards this end, we propose the use of natural language processing technology
 to analyze Arabic language data streams from social media websites.
 The goal is to interpret what people are discussing and what is the general
 mood about these topics.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
The system is designed to analyze Arabic language data streams from social
 media and extract useful information such as what topics are people discussing,
 which topics are of most interest, and what are people's sentiment about
 these topics in terms of approval or disapproval.
 For now we will focus on Twitter feeds.
 This tool will help in the market of social media analytics.
 This market grows considerably, and it now has many applications such as
 public mood tracking for the purposes of homeland security, gauging potential
 customers, marketing applications, and consumer confidence estimation for
 the purpose of assessing the economy.
 It will also help build a base of expertise for Arabic NLP technologies
 in Egypt.
 We will also collect and annotate a dataset for Arabic language subjectivity
 and sentiment analysis, that is annotated at the sentence level for subjectivit
y and sentiment polarity.
\end_layout

