\color none

\begin_inset Formula $nearHit_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the closest pattern to 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{i}$
\end_inset

 in the same class and nearMiss
\begin_inset Formula $_{i,c}$
\end_inset

 is the closest miss pattern to 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{i}$
\end_inset

 in class 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 (miss class).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Class Separation Feature selection: 
\series default
This method ranks features by estimating the class means 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{ik}$
\end_inset

 for each feature 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 and class 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

.
 Then it estimates the class feature standard deviation 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{ik}$
\end_inset

 for each feature 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 and class 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

, and at the end it measures the feature separation by the following equation:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
H_{i}=\sum_{k^{'}=1,k!=k^{'}}^{K}\sum_{k=1}^{K}[\frac{|m_{i}(k)-m_{i}(k^{'})|}{s_{i}(k)+s_{i}(k^{'})}]
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $k'$
\end_inset

 run over the number of classes, 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{i}(k)$
\end_inset

 is the mean of feature 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 for class
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{i}(k)$
\end_inset

 is the standard deviation for feature 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 for class 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

.
 If the means are far away (normalized by standard deviation of all points)
 then there is good separability, and the feature is good.
\end_layout

